  "Aperol|Crab Cake": "Aperol with crab cake — softest amaro against delicate crab. Works; this is the one amaro in the family gentle enough to sit alongside crab — not a featured match, but it doesn't overpower.",
  "Aperol|Creamed Spinach": "Aperol's crisp bitter-orange-aperitivo edge overpowers the creamed spinach's rich bechamel-laced greens -- the plate deserves Porterhouse, Keenan Chardonnay, or Far Niente Chardonnay, not a bitter aperitivo. Avoid; reach for any of those instead. Hold the Aperol for the steak course.",
  "Aperol|Creamy Potato": "Aperol's crisp bitter-orange-aperitivo edge overpowers the potato soup's silky-bodied cream -- the plate deserves Far Niente Chardonnay, Keenan Chardonnay, or Jean-Pierre Grossot Chablis, not a bitter aperitivo. Avoid; steer the table to the alternatives. Hold the Aperol for the steak course.",
