  "Basil Hayden's 10 Year|Tuxedo-Crusted Yellowfin Tuna": "Basil Hayden's 10 Year's oak-and-vanilla bourbon depth overpowers the tuna's seared-rare flesh with sesame crust -- the plate deserves Pommery Cuvée Louise, Jean-Pierre Grossot Chablis, or Elk Cove Pinot Blanc, not a bourbon. Avoid; the alts above are the call. Save the Basil Hayden's 10 Year for the steak course.",
  "Basil Hayden's 10 Year|Vegetable Curry with Chickpeas": "Basil Hayden's 10 Year's oak-and-vanilla bourbon depth sits alongside the curry's spiced chickpea-curry warmth: the bourbon backbone carries the curry, and the rounded sweetness brightens the bowl. Works; high proof over-specified for the soup.",
  "Basil Hayden's Malted Rye|Asparagus": "Basil Hayden's Malted Rye's rye-spice character finds neutral with the asparagus' green-vegetal edge: the rye backbone drives the asparagus, and the dry-spice register brightens the side. Works; the bourbon's character is distinctive but the pairing isn't a standout.",
  "Basil Hayden's Malted Rye|Au Gratin Potatoes": "Basil Hayden's Malted Rye with au gratin potatoes — malted grain against cheese-and-cream. Bread-and-dairy again; the pairing works on grain logic in a way wheated bourbons don't touch. Strong; reliable across the meal.",
  "Basil Hayden's Malted Rye|Beignets": "Basil Hayden's Malted Rye's rye-spice character reads alongside the beignets' warm sugar-dusted pastry: the rye backbone drives the beignets, and the spice threads the dessert. Works; Remus 15 handles dessert density at Gatsby-tribute register.",
  "Basil Hayden's Malted Rye|Bone Marrow": "Basil Hayden's Malted Rye with bone marrow — bready malted grain against umami fat. Distinctive but outmatched by Weller 12 on weight; the pour's character is the draw, not the match for marrow's intensity. Strong; consistent recommendation across the table.",
  "Basil Hayden's Malted Rye|Bone-In Filet": "Basil Hayden's Malted Rye's rye-spice character sits alongside the bone-in filet's bone-enhanced buttery tenderness: the rye spice cuts the bone-enhanced filet, and the rye edge frames the cut. Strong; accessible everyday match.",
  "Basil Hayden's Malted Rye|Broccoli Cheddar": "Basil Hayden's Malted Rye's rye-spice character finds neutral with the broccoli cheddar's cheddar-and-broccoli cream: the rye-and-oak weight handles the broccoli cheddar, and the oak rounds the cream. Works; Parker's Heritage 16th handles the richness at annual-release register.",
  "Basil Hayden's Malted Rye|Broccolini": "Basil Hayden's Malted Rye's rye-spice character finds neutral with the broccolini's tender green stalks: the rye-and-oak weight handles the broccolini, and the rye-grain bite cuts the side. Works; bold intensity slightly over-specified.",
  "Basil Hayden's Malted Rye|Brussels and Belly": "Basil Hayden's Malted Rye with Brussels + Belly — spicy-sweet malted rye meets maple-glazed pork belly. The bready character picks up the Brussels' char and the pork belly's maple; distinctive and specifically Basil Hayden's Malted Rye. Excellent; reliable headline pairing.",
  "Basil Hayden's Malted Rye|Burrata": "Basil Hayden's Malted Rye with burrata — fresh dairy against bready malted. Avoid; the pour's character can't find the burrata's gentleness.",
  "Basil Hayden's Malted Rye|Butternut Squash": "Basil Hayden's Malted Rye's rye-spice character sits alongside the butternut squash's silky sweet squash cream: the rye-and-oak weight handles the squash bisque, and the oak softens the cream. Works; Portwood is over-specified for sides.",
  "Basil Hayden's Malted Rye|Carrot Cake": "Basil Hayden's Malted Rye with carrot cake — spicy-sweet malted rye against cream cheese and cinnamon. The malted character and cake warmth find common ground; a distinctive within-family dessert pairing. Strong; the pairing reads at register.",
  "Basil Hayden's Malted Rye|Cheesecake": "Basil Hayden's Malted Rye with cheesecake — bready malted notes against custard. Works; the bread-and-custard pairing is capable without being remarkable.",
  "Basil Hayden's Malted Rye|Chilean Seabass": "Basil Hayden's Malted Rye's rye-spice character overpowers the seabass' buttery seabass flesh -- the plate deserves Far Niente Chardonnay, Pommery Cuvée Louise, or Keenan Chardonnay, not a rye whiskey. Avoid; the alts above are the call. Basil Hayden's Malted Rye belongs on the steak course.",
  "Basil Hayden's Malted Rye|Chocolate Brownie": "Basil Hayden's Malted Rye with the chocolate brownie — malted grain against cocoa. Works; for chocolate interplay, Basil Hayden's Toast is the family call.",
  "Basil Hayden's Malted Rye|Chocolate Cake": "Basil Hayden's Malted Rye's rye-spice character sits alongside the chocolate cake's layered chocolate body: the high-rye spice register matches the chocolate cake, and the spice threads the dessert. Works; safe bourbon-on-hearty-soup alongside, but not the headline call.",
  "Basil Hayden's Malted Rye|Clam Chowder": "Basil Hayden's Malted Rye's rye-spice character leans against the chowder's creamy clam-and-potato base: the rye backbone drives the chowder, and the oak threads the cream. Works; Fortuna's NZ terroir meets the glaze at distinctive register.",
